        <hl1>Big and Little Talks</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Teaching Teenagers a Subject Many Know All Too Well'' (Oct. 10), discusses getting ''through the Big Talk.'' But why have a Big Talk? Why not have lots of Little Talks, or better yet, an Ongoing Conversation? Also, the article states that ''hooking up'' ''means having oral sex.'' This is not always true. Sometimes ''hooking up'' means getting together or just kissing. (And sometimes a cigar is just a cigar.)</p>
        <p>CAROL WESTON  New York</p>
      </block>
